The <strong><code>position</code></strong> <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS" title="CSS">CSS</a> property sets how an element is positioned in a document. The <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/top" title="The top CSS property participates in specifying the vertical position of a positioned element. It has no effect on non-positioned elements."><code>top</code></a>, <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/right" title="The right CSS property participates in specifying the horizontal position of a positioned element. It has no effect on non-positioned elements."><code>right</code></a>, <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/bottom" title="The bottom CSS property participates in setting the vertical position of a positioned element. It has no effect on non-positioned elements."><code>bottom</code></a>, and <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/left" title="The left CSS property participates in specifying the horizontal position of a positioned element. It has no effect on non-positioned elements."><code>left</code></a> properties determine the final location of positioned elements.